# Complete Government Authority Journey and Workflow

## Scenario

The Ministry of Health and Family Welfare of Bangladesh operates as the Supreme Authority of the National Unified Digital Healthcare Ecosystem.

Unlike doctors who provide treatment and hospitals that manage healthcare operations, the Government Authority is responsible for governing, regulating, monitoring, analyzing, planning, and improving the entire healthcare system of the nation.

The Government Authority does not directly treat patients. Instead, it oversees the complete healthcare infrastructure of the country.

This document describes the complete workflow of the Government Authority.

---

# Phase 1: National Healthcare Governance

## Supreme Authority Role

The Government Authority acts as the parent authority of the ecosystem.

Hierarchy:

```text
Government Authority
    │
    ├── Public Hospitals
    ├── Private Hospitals
    ├── Clinics
    ├── Diagnostic Centers
    ├── Pharmacies
    ├── Medical Colleges
    └── Healthcare Professionals
```

Every healthcare entity ultimately falls under government supervision.

